e EBITDA margin to 13.6% from 12.9% a year earlier. For 2025, adjusted EBITDA rose 28.3% to $180 million, with adjusted EPS advancing 28.3% in Q4 to $1.77 and 18.4% for the year to $6.23.\n\n## Personal Care Growth Outpaces Expectations [...] ## \n\n## Latest in\n\n## More\n\n# Addus HomeCare Earnings Call Highlights Growth And Scale\n\nAddus HomeCare Corporation ((ADUS)) has held its Q4 earnings call. Read on for the main highlights of the call.\n\n### Claim 50% Off TipRanks Premium\n\nAddus HomeCare’s latest earnings call struck an upbeat tone, with management emphasizing robust revenue growth, expanding profitability and a strengthened balance sheet. While they acknowledged pockets of pressure in margins, home health and working capital, the overall message was that strategic acquisitions, rate increases and operational investments are driving sustainable momentum.\n\n## Robust Revenue Growth Across Quarter and Full Year', 'score': 0.92604345, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.investing.com/news/earnings/addus-homecare-earnings-up-next-as-investors-eye-acquisition-talk-93CH-4519232', 'title': 'Addus HomeCare earnings up next as investors eye ...', 'content': '# Addus HomeCare earnings up next as investors eye acquisition talk\n\nBy\n\nEarnings\n\nPublished 02/23/2026, 10:04 AM\n\nAddus HomeCare earnings up next as investors eye acquisition talk\n\nView all comments (0)0\n\n&copy; Reuters.\n\n© Reuters.\n\nADUS-0.74%\n\nAddus HomeCare Corporation reports fourth-quarter results Monday after the market close, with analysts expecting the home healthcare provider to post another quarter of robust growth—and watching closely for signals on potential deal-making.\n\nAnalysts project revenue of $372.9 million, up 25.5% year over year, and earnings of $1.72 per share, representing a 24.6% increase from the prior year. If the company meets forecasts, it would mark sequential gains from the third quarter, when Addus posted EPS of $1.56 and revenue of $362.3 million. [...] Analysts rate the stock a buy with a mean price target of $141, implying 22% upside from the current price of $115.48. Analyst estimates have remained largely stable over the past 30 days, with both EPS and revenue forecasts essentially flat over the past week and two months.\n\nWhat Investors Are Watching\n\nThe big question heading into the print is whether management will discuss progress on merger and acquisition opportunities. KeyBanc analyst Matthew Gillmor noted that the stock may require a catalyst and expressed optimism that "a large PC acquisition may be possible in 2026." With Addus expected to benefit from rate increases in Texas and other key personal care states, investors will look for updated guidance on how these tailwinds affect organic growth projections for 2026. [...] Recent Performance\n\nIn the third quarter, Addus beat analysts’ revenue expectations with $362.3 million, up 25% year over year, and also exceeded EPS estimates. The company has delivered consistent execution, though it has missed Wall Street’s revenue estimates multiple times over the last two years.\n\nThe home healthcare sector faces both opportunities and challenges heading into 2026. Demand for home-based services remains strong as the aging population grows and healthcare delivery continues moving closer to the home, but workforce shortages continue to challenge agencies by increasing labor costs and limiting service capacity.\n\nFor Addus, Monday’s report will test whether the company can sustain its growth trajectory while providing the strategic clarity investors are seeking.', 'score': 0.9147261, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.directorstalkinterviews.com/addus-homecare-corporation-adus-investor-outlook-with-a-36-potential-upside/4121243817', 'title': 'Addus HomeCare Corporation (ADUS): Investor Outlook ...', 'content': 'One of the standout features of Addus HomeCare is its impressive revenue growth rate of 25.60%. This growth is a testament to the company’s effectiveness in expanding its service offerings and capturing market share in a competitive industry. With earnings per share (EPS) of 5.22 and a return on equity (ROE) of 9.33%, the company demonstrates its ability to generate profits and deliver value to shareholders. Furthermore, the company’s free cash flow of $72.16 million provides a solid foundation for future investments and potential expansions. [...] Currently trading at $102.86, Addus HomeCare’s stock price is comfortably positioned within its 52-week range of $89.83 to $122.75. Despite a recent price change of -0.35, the stock holds substantial promise for investors, as indicated by its robust potential upside of 36.33%. Analysts have set a target price range between $112.00 and $160.00, with an average target of $140.23, signaling confidence in the company’s growth trajectory. [...] When considering valuation metrics, Addus HomeCare’s forward P/E ratio stands at 13.81, which could indicate a relatively attractive valuation for a company with its growth rate. However, the absence of a trailing P/E, PEG ratio, and other valuation metrics could suggest complexities in assessing the company’s past financial performance.\n\nInvestors should note that Addus HomeCare does not offer a dividend, as indicated by its 0.00% payout ratio, which might appeal to those focused on capital appreciation rather than income generation. The lack of a dividend yield can be interpreted as a strategic decision by the company to reinvest earnings into growth initiatives.', 'score': 0.90123636, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.stocktitan.net/financials/ADUS/', 'title': 'ADUS - Addus Homecare Corp Financials - Stock Titan', 'content': "Profitability 49\n\nAddus Homecare Corp has an operating margin of 9.7%, meaning the company retains $10 of operating profit per $100 of revenue. This results in a moderate score of 49/100, indicating healthy but not exceptional operating efficiency. This is up from 8.9% the prior 