2026-03-25 05:37:37 | DEBUG    | src/search_service.py:300 | [Tavily] 原始响应: {'query': '3M Company earnings revenue profit growth forecast', 'follow_up_questions': None, 'answer': None, 'images': [], 'results': [{'url': 'https://site.financialmodelingprep.com/market-news/3m-companys-earnings-overview-and-future-outlook', 'title': "3M Company's Earnings Overview and Future Outlook | FMP", 'content': "3M's fourth-quarter performance showed adjusted earnings of $1.83 per share on revenue of $6.1 billion, both exceeding analyst expectations. However, the stock is down 3.8% at $161.43, partly due to a broad-market selloff. The stock has been trading within a narrow range since reaching a three-year peak of $174.69 on December 3, but it has increased by 14.1% year over year.\n\nThe company's financial results for the fourth quarter and full year of 2025 reveal a mixed performance. While GAAP sales increased by 2.1% year-over-year to $6.1 billion, the operating margin decreased by 510 basis points to 13.0%. On an adjusted basis, sales were $6.0 billion with an organic growth of 2.2%, and the adjusted operating margin improved by 140 basis points to 21.1%. [...] 3M Company (NYSE:MMM) is a diversified technology company known for its wide range of products, including adhesives, abrasives, and personal protective equipment. The company operates in various sectors, such as healthcare, consumer goods, and industrial products. 3M faces competition from companies like Honeywell and DuPont in the industrial and consumer markets.\n\nOn January 20, 2026, 3M reported earnings per share (EPS) of $1.83, surpassing the estimated $1.81. The company generated a revenue of $6.1 billion, suprassing estimated $6.008 billion. Despite this earnings beat, 3M's stock is experiencing a decline, as highlighted by Barron's. The stock is under pressure due to disappointing profit forecasts for 2026, which have fallen short of estimates. [...] # 3M Company's Earnings Overview and Future Outlook\n\nBy Tony Dante\n\nJan 20, 2026\n\nGet More MMMData\n\nFMP API\n\nCompany ProfileFinancial StatementsAnalyst EstimatesDividends\n\n 3M Company (NYSE:MMM) reported earnings per share (EPS) of $1.83, surpassing estimates.\n The company's revenue was $6.1 billion, with a year-over-year increase in GAAP sales.\n Despite a positive earnings beat, 3M's stock is under pressure due to disappointing profit forecasts for 2026.", 'score': 0.99992156, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://simplywall.st/stocks/us/capital-goods/nyse-mmm/3m/future', 'title': '3M (NYSE:MMM) Stock Forecast & Analyst Predictions - Simply Wall St', 'content': "3M Company\n\nNYSE:MMM Stock Report\n\nMarket Cap: US$87.1b\n\n# 3M Future Growth\n\n## Future criteria checks 2/6\n\n3M is forecast to grow earnings and revenue by 10.4% and 2.5% per annum respectively. EPS is expected to grow by 10.7% per annum. Return on equity is forecast to be 44.3% in 3 years.\n\n## Key information\n\n10.4%\n\nEarnings growth rate\n\n10.73%\n\nEPS growth rate\n\n|  |  |\n --- |\n| Industrials earnings growth | 12.3% |\n| Revenue growth rate | 2.5% |\n| Future return on equity | 44.26% |\n| Analyst coverage | Good |\n| Last updated | 27 Feb 2026 |\n\nGood\n\n## Recent future growth updates\n\n### 3M Company Revises Earnings Guidance for the Full Year 2025\n\n### 3M Company Provides Earnings Guidance for the Year 2025\n\n### Consensus EPS estimates increase by 10% [...] ## Analyst Future Growth Forecasts\n\nEarnings vs Savings Rate: MMM's forecast earnings growth (10.4% per year) is above the savings rate (3.4%).\n\nEarnings vs Market: MMM's earnings (10.4% per year) are forecast to grow slower than the US market (15.5% per year).\n\nHigh Growth Earnings: MMM's earnings are forecast to grow, but not significantly.\n\nRevenue vs Market: MMM's revenue (2.5% per year) is forecast to grow slower than the US market (10.2% per year).\n\nHigh Growth Revenue: MMM's revenue (2.5% per year) is forecast to grow slower than 20% per year.\n\n## Earnings per Share Growth Forecasts\n\n## Future Return on Equity\n\nFuture ROE: MMM's Return on Equity is forecast to be very high in 3 years time (44.3%).\n\n## Discover growth companies\n\n7D\n\n1Y\n\n7D\n\n1Y\n\n7D\n\n1Y [...] | Date | Revenue | Earnings | Free Cash Flow | Cash from Op | Avg. No. Analysts |\n ---  ---  --- |\n| 12/31/2028 | 26,745 | 4,888 | 4,458 | 5,454 | 4 |\n| 12/31/2027 | 25,985 | 4,798 | 3,738 | 3,991 | 13 |\n| 12/31/2026 | 25,152 | 4,452 | 3,775 | 4,741 | 13 |\n| 12/31/2025 | 24,948 | 3,250 | 1,396 | 2,306 | N/A |\n| 9/30/2025 | 24,825 | 3,401 | 1,588 | 2,541 | N/A |\n| 6/30/2025 | 24,602 | 3,939 | -1,983 | -1,002 | N/A |\n| 3/31/2025 | 24,513 | 4,420 | -69 | 973 | N/A |\n| 12/31/2024 | 24,575 | 4,009 | 638 | 1,819 | N/A |\n| 9/30/2024 | 24,567 | 3,915 | 739 | 1,987 | N/A |\n| 6/30/2024 | 24,543 | 16 | 4,277 | 5,684 | N/A |\n| 3/31/2024 | 24,571 | -8,359 | 4,657 | 6,172 | N/A |\n| 12/31/2023 | 24,610 | -8,402 | 5,065 | 6,680 | N/A |\n| 9/30/2023 | 26,687 | -8,495 | 4,853 | 6,616 | N/A |", 'score': 0.9998766, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://mlq.ai/news/3m-beats-q4-earnings-estimates-but-shares-plunge-on-tepid-2026-guidance/', 'title': '3M Beats Q4 Earnings Estimates but Shares Plunge on Tepid 2026 ...', 'content': "## Execution Risks in 2026 Sales Growth Guidance\n\n3M's 2026 guidance projects adjusted EPS growth to $8.50-$8.70 from $8.06 in 2025, with 4% sales growth supported by $875 million in volume and productivity benefits across segments, though offset by PFAS-related costs, stranded expenses, tariffs and $225 million in investments. Management emphasized tracking ahead of medium-term targets from last year's Investor Day, building on 2025's foundation of improved on-time delivery above 90% and reduced poor quality costs by 100 basis points. Free cash flow conversion above 100% annually positions the company for continued shareholder returns, but soft consumer and electronics demand could challenge execution.\n\n### Companies Mentioned\n\n3M Company Logo\n\n#### 3M Company\n\nMMM NYSE [...] 3M Co. reported fourth-quarter 2025 adjusted earnings per share of $1.83, exceeding analyst expectations of $1.80, though adjusted sales of $6.0 billion fell short of the $6.03 billion forecast. Shares fell about 7% following guidance for fiscal 2026 adjusted EPS of $8.50 to $8.70 and roughly 4% sales growth.\n\n## Quarterly Financial Results [...] # 3M Beats Q4 Earnings Estimates but Shares Plunge on Tepid 2026 Guidance\n\nJanuary 21, 2026 at 2:01 PM • by  MLQ Agent\n\n#### Key Points\n\n 3M posted Q4 adjusted EPS of $1.83, beating estimates of $1.80, with adjusted sales of $6.0 billion slightly below $6.03 billion forecast.\n Full-year 2025 adjusted EPS reached $8.06, up 10% year-over-year, with organic sales growth of 2.1%.\n 2026 guidance calls for adjusted EPS of $8.50-$8.70 and about 4% sales growth, prompting a 7% share decline.\n Safety and Industrial segment grew 3.8% organically in Q4; Consumer segment declined 2.2%.\n Company returned $4.8 billion to shareholders in 2025 via dividends and repurchases.\n\n3M Beats Q4 Earnings Estimates but Shares Plunge on Tepid 2026 Guidance", 'score': 0.9997241, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.quiverquant.com/news/3M+falls+as+2026+outlook+and+revenue+picture+overshadow+Q4+profit+beat', 'title': '3M falls as 2026 outlook and revenue picture overshadow Q4 profit ...', 'content': "Details:- 3M reported fourth-quarter and full-year 2025 results and initiated full-year 2026 financial guidance in its earnings materials.\n- The company guided to 2026 adjusted EPS of $8.50 to $8.70 and approximately 3% organic sales growth, which some investors viewed as conservative versus expectations.\n- Management highlighted strong cash conversion and continued capital returns (including planned share repurchases), but that support was not enough to offset concerns about the outlook.\n- This could also be amplified by broader market risk-off trading, where “good-but-not-great” guidance can prompt quick profit-taking after a prior run-up.\n\nSources:\n\n3M Investor Relations, MarketBeat, Schaeffer's Research [...] Download our data to use for your own analysis\n\nNancy Pelosi Profile\nMarkwayne Mullin Profile\nJ. D. Vance Profile\nQuiver Logo\nQuiver Logo\n\n# 3M falls as 2026 outlook and revenue picture overshadow Q4 profit beat\n\nBy: Quiver PriceTracker\n\nNone\n\n3M Company (MMM) is down 3.9% today. Here is some analysis on what might have caused this price movement.\n\nAnalysis: The move appears tied to investor reaction to 3M’s latest quarterly results and, more importantly, its initial full-year 2026 outlook. Even with better-than-expected adjusted earnings and solid cash generation, the market seemed to focus on a softer revenue trajectory and guidance that left little room for upside.", 'score': 0.999566, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.tikr.com/blog/3m-fell-4-this-week-heres-how-much-the-stock-could-rise-by-2026', 'title': "3M Fell 4% This Week. Here's How Much the Stock Could Rise by ...", 'content': '3M’s revenue outlook reflects a gradual recovery as the company benefits from stronger industrial demand, improved pricing discipline, and growth from new product introductions across its safety, electronics, and advanced materials businesses.\n\n3M Company stock\n\nMMM Revenue & Analyst Growth Estimates Over Five Years\n\nOperational improvements are expected to play a major role in the earnings trajectory. Management’s focus on commercial excellence, manufacturing efficiency, and cost reductions could continue expanding margins toward the mid-20% range, which would significantly increase earnings power. [...] This week, 3M also reported fourth-quarter results that showed steady operational progress. The company delivered 2.2% organic sales growth, 21.1% adjusted operating margin, and $1.83 in earnings per share, while guiding for about 3% organic sales growth in 2026 with EPS expected between $8.50 and $8.70.   \n  \nCEO Bill Brown said, “We delivered solid results in Q4,” noting that growth was driven by strength in safety, electronics, and industrial businesses even as consumer markets remained soft. [...] Analyst commentary added another layer to the story. Wolfe Research raised its price target on 3M to $205 from $196 and maintained an Outperform rating, implying roughly 24% upside from recent levels.   \n  \nThe company also announced a 6.8% dividend increase to $0.78 per share, while Chief Accounting Officer Theresa Reinseth sold 5,145 shares at about $172.75, a transaction worth roughly $889,000, which some investors viewed as profit taking after the stock’s recent rebound.\n\n3M Company stock\n\nMMM Guided Valuation Model\n\nSee analysts’ growth forecasts and price targets for 3M Company (It’s free) >>>\n\n## Is MMM Undervalued?\n\nUnder valuation assumptions, the stock is modeled using:\n\n Revenue Growth (CAGR): 3.3%\n Operating Margins: 25.1%\n Exit P/E Multiple: 17x', 'score': 0.99937856, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://finance.yahoo.com/news/3m-issues-2026-outlook-profit-164911132.html', 'title': '3M Issues 2026 Outlook as Profit Guidance Misses Estimates', 'content': 'MMM\n\n+3.80%\n\nThis article first appeared on GuruFocus.\n\n3M (NYSE:MMM) set a more cautious tone for 2026 after issuing profit guidance that came in narrowly below Wall Street expectations, highlighting the friction facing its turnaround in an uneven economic backdrop. The company said adjusted earnings are expected to range between $8.50 and $8.70 per share next year, with the midpoint slightly under the $8.64 consensus estimate, while adjusted sales are projected to grow about 4%. The outlook followed a fourth quarter in which adjusted earnings reached $1.83 per share, modestly ahead of forecasts, even as adjusted operating margins of 21.1% fell just short of expectations.', 'score': 0.9992084, 'raw_content': None}], 'response_time': 1.57, 'request_id': '9437e030-82cc-495e-8a6a-6cffa80641f5'}
