2026-03-25 05:38:38 | DEBUG    | src/search_service.py:300 | [Tavily] 原始响应: {'query': 'Costco Wholesale Corporation earnings revenue profit growth forecast', 'follow_up_questions': None, 'answer': None, 'images': [], 'results': [{'url': 'https://capital.com/en-int/market-updates/costco-stock-forecast-02-03-2026', 'title': 'Costco Stock Forecast | Upcoming Q2 2026 Earnings - Capital.com', 'content': '### MarketBeat (coverage and consensus context)\n\nMarketBeat reports that, following new coverage in late February 2026, Costco carries an overall analyst consensus described as ‘Moderate Buy’, with a mean Wall Street price target of about $1,014.39. The piece notes that this average follows an earnings release showing year-on-year revenue growth of roughly 8.3% and an earnings-per-share beat, while analysts reference membership trends and institutional ownership patterns as supportive factors (MarketBeat, 27 February 2026). [...] PERSONALPROFESSIONALPARTNERS\n\nSUPPORT\n\nen\n\nOpen platformuser\n\nHomeCostco stock forecast: Upcoming Q2 2026 earnings\n\n# Costco stock forecast: Upcoming Q2 2026 earnings\n\nCostco is a US-listed wholesale retailer, with attention on its upcoming quarterly earnings and expectations for steady comparable sales and membership income growth. Explore third-party COST price targets and technical analysis.\n\nBy Dan Mitchell\n\nPhoto: Shutterstock.com\n\nCostco (COST) is trading at $1,002.86 as of 9:40am UTC on 2 March 2026, moving within an intraday range of $980.95–1,009.31. The shares are hovering near the upper end of that band after rebounding from the session low, with price action contained below the day’s high. Past performance is not a reliable indicator of future results. [...] ### MarketScreener (broker consensus)\n\nMarketScreener reports that broker consensus implies an average 12-month price target of around $1,049.53, compared with a recent close near $1,011.17, and a mean rating described as ‘Outperform’. The service notes that this consensus sits within a range of individual targets and reflects expectations for steady earnings and revenue growth, supported by Costco’s warehouse expansion strategy and membership-driven business model (MarketScreener, 20 February 2026).\n\n### VCP Scanner (Wall Street target summary)', 'score': 0.8005209, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.investing.com/news/transcripts/earnings-call-transcript-costco-q2-2026-beats-forecasts-stock-dips-93CH-4545772', 'title': 'Earnings call transcript: Costco Q2 2026 beats forecasts, stock dips', 'content': 'Gary Millerchip, Chief Financial Officer, Costco Wholesale Corporation: Thanks, Ron. In today’s press release, we reported operating results for the second quarter of fiscal year 2026, the 12 weeks ending February 15th. As usual, we published a slide deck under Events and Presentations on our investor website with supplemental information to support today’s press release. Net income for the second quarter came in at $2.035 billion or $4.58 per diluted share, up nearly 14% from $1.788 billion or $4.02 per diluted share in the second quarter last year. Net sales for the second quarter were $68.24 billion, an increase of 9.1% from $62.53 billion in Q2 2025. [...] Gary Millerchip, Chief Financial Officer, Costco Wholesale Corporation: Thanks, Rupesh. Maybe again, just taking a step back, big picture, we were pleased with the membership results for the quarter. We saw, I think you heard us say in the prepared remarks, 7.5% growth in membership fee income. If you adjust out the fee increase in FX, so underlying really strong member loyalty and member fee income growth during the quarter. The bigger sort of part of that was the 9% growth in upgrades, which I think shows that the impact of the $10 Instacart credit that we’re offering each month for online shopping and the extended hours and some of the other benefits that we’ve added are resonating with our members and increasing the level of upgrades. [...] We reported membership fee income of $1.355 billion, an increase of $162 million or 13.6% year-over-year. Adjusting for FX, the increase was 12.2%. The September 2024 U.S. and Canada membership fee increase accounted for about one-third of our membership income growth. Excluding the membership fee increase and FX, membership income grew 7.5% year-over-year. This was driven by continued growth in our membership base and upgrades to executive memberships. At Q2 end, we had 40.4 million paid executive memberships, up 9.5% versus last year. We ended the quarter with 82.1 million total paid members, up 4.8% versus last year, and 147.2 million cardholders, up 4.7% year-over-year.', 'score': 0.7156829, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.stocktitan.net/sec-filings/COST/10-q-costco-wholesale-corp-new-quarterly-earnings-report-f7b450ede14b.html', 'title': 'Costco Q2 2026 earnings: sales up 9% | COST SEC Filing - Form 10-Q', 'content': '|  |  |\n --- |\n| 12 Weeks Ended | 24 Weeks Ended |\n| February 15, 2026 | February 16, 2025 | February 15, 2026 | February 16, 2025 |\n| REVENUE |\n| Net sales | $ | 68,242 | $ | 62,530 | $ | 134,220 | $ | 123,515 |\n| Membership fees | 1,355 | 1,193 | 2,684 | 2,359 |\n| Total revenue | 69,597 | 63,723 | 136,904 | 125,874 |\n| OPERATING EXPENSES |\n| Merchandise costs | 60,719 | 55,744 | 119,229 | 109,853 |\n| Selling, general and administrative | 6,272 | 5,663 | 12,606 | 11,509 |\n| Operating income | 2,606 | 2,316 | 5,069 | 4,512 |\n| OTHER INCOME (EXPENSE) |\n| Interest expense | (33) | (36) | (68) | (73) |\n| Interest income and other, net | 148 | 142 | 303 | 289 |\n| INCOME BEFORE INCOME TAXES | 2,721 | 2,422 | 5,304 | 4,728 |\n| Provision for income taxes | 686 | 634 | 1,268 | 1,142 | [...] |  |  |\n --- |\n| 12 Weeks Ended | 24 Weeks Ended |\n| February 15, 2026 | February 16, 2025 | February 15, 2026 | February 16, 2025 |\n| United States |\n| Total revenue | $ | 49,931 | $ | 46,413 | $ | 98,500 | $ | 91,501 |\n| Merchandise costs | 43