2026-03-25 05:39:08 | DEBUG    | src/search_service.py:300 | [Tavily] 原始响应: {'query': 'AbbVie Inc. earnings revenue profit growth forecast', 'follow_up_questions': None, 'answer': None, 'images': [], 'results': [{'url': 'https://www.gurufocus.com/news/8578283/abbvie-abbv-set-for-earnings-surge-with-key-developments-ahead', 'title': 'AbbVie (ABBV) Set for Earnings Surge with Key ...', 'content': "AbbVie (ABBV) is poised to announce a 23% increase in fourth-quarter earnings, with EPS projected at $2.65 and revenue expected to rise 8.7% to $16.41 billion. The company anticipates a $1.3 billion charge from acquired IPR&D and milestone expenses, impacting EPS by -$0.71. Despite 12 downward EPS revisions, revenue estimates saw 12 upward adjustments. Analysts highlight strong performance due to Skyrizi and Rinvoq, with future growth anticipated. Intense competition in IBD, notably from JNJ's Tremfya, and strategic deals in 2026 are pivotal for AbbVie's growth trajectory. [...] Image 4: Article's Main Image\n\nKey Takeaways:\n\n   AbbVie ABBV projects a significant 23% increase in fourth-quarter earnings.\n   Revenue is expected to rise by 8.7% to $16.41 billion, despite a $1.3 billion charge impacting EPS.\n   Strong performance driven by Skyrizi and Rinvoq, with strategic growth anticipated in 2026. [...] by QuoteMedia, Inc. (CSI). Company fundamental data is provided by Morningstar. Analyst estimates data is sourced from both Refinitiv and Morningstar, with priority given to Refinitiv data. Data is updated daily.", 'score': 0.99999213, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://simplywall.st/stocks/us/pharmaceuticals-biotech/nyse-abbv/abbvie/future', 'title': 'AbbVie (NYSE:ABBV) Stock Forecast & Analyst Predictions', 'content': "AbbVie Inc.\n\nNYSE:ABBV Stock Report\n\nMarket Cap: US$402.2b\n\n# AbbVie Future Growth\n\n## Future criteria checks 4/6\n\nAbbVie is forecast to grow earnings and revenue by 22.5% and 6.3% per annum respectively. EPS is expected to grow by 23.7% per annum. Return on equity is forecast to be 182.7% in 3 years.\n\n## Key information\n\n22.5%\n\nEarnings growth rate\n\n23.71%\n\nEPS growth rate\n\n|  |  |\n --- |\n| Biotechs earnings growth | 23.5% |\n| Revenue growth rate | 6.3% |\n| Future return on equity | 182.70% |\n| Analyst coverage | Good |\n| Last updated | 09 Mar 2026 |\n\nGood\n\n## Recent future growth updates\n\n### Consensus EPS estimates increase by 45%\n\n### Consensus EPS estimates increase by 14%\n\n### Consensus EPS estimates fall by 36%\n\n### Consensus EPS estimates fall by 11% [...] ## Analyst Future Growth Forecasts\n\nEarnings vs Savings Rate: ABBV's forecast earnings growth (22.5% per year) is above the savings rate (3.4%).\n\nEarnings vs Market: ABBV's earnings (22.5% per year) are forecast to grow faster than the US market (15.7% per year).\n\nHigh Growth Earnings: ABBV's earnings are expected to grow significantly over the next 3 years.\n\nRevenue vs Market: ABBV's revenue (6.3% per year) is forecast to grow slower than the US market (10.4% per year).\n\nHigh Growth Revenue: ABBV's revenue (6.3% per year) is forecast to grow slower than 20% per year.\n\n## Earnings per Share Growth Forecasts\n\n## Future Return on Equity\n\nFuture ROE: ABBV's Return on Equity is forecast to be very high in 3 years time (182.7%).\n\n## Discover growth companies\n\n7D\n\n1Y\n\n7D\n\n1Y\n\n7D\n\n1Y [...] | Date | Revenue | Earnings | Free Cash Flow | Cash from Op | Avg. No. Analysts |\n ---  ---  --- |\n| 12/31/2028 | 77,742 | 22,812 | 30,859 | 31,289 | 21 |\n| 12/31/2027 | 72,530 | 20,041 | 28,237 | 29,342 | 27 |\n| 12/31/2026 | 67,076 | 17,187 | 24,592 | 26,198 | 27 |\n| 12/31/2025 | 61,160 | 4,186 | 17,816 | 19,030 | N/A |\n| 9/30/2025 | 59,644 | 2,348 | 19,684 | 20,860 | N/A |\n| 6/30/2025 | 58,328 | 3,723 | 18,239 | 19,283 | N/A |\n| 3/31/2025 | 57,367 | 4,155 | 15,385 | 16,401 | N/A |\n| 12/31/2024 | 56,334 | 4,238 | 17,832 | 18,806 | N/A |\n| 9/30/2024 | 55,533 | 5,081 | 15,623 | 16,511 | N/A |\n| 6/30/2024 | 55,000 | 5,298 | 17,780 | 18,638 | N/A |\n| 3/31/2024 | 54,403 | 5,951 | 21,891 | 22,686 | N/A |\n| 12/31/2023 | 54,318 | 4,820 | 22,062 | 22,839 | N/A |", 'score': 0.99996996, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.pharmexec.com/view/abbvie-raises-2025-profit-forecast-increased-demand-immunology-treatments', 'title': 'AbbVie Raises 2025 Profit Forecast Following Increased ...', 'content': '# What is AbbVie raising its 2025 profit forecast to?\n\nAbbVie is expected to raise its 2025 annual profit-per-share amount from between $10.38 and $10.58 to $10.61 and $10.65.1The raise comes as a reaction to the company’s quarterly sales, which reached $15.78 billion worldwide for the third quarter, a 9.1% increase on reported basis, and a 8.4% increase on an operational basis.2During the entire quarter, AbbVie noted that Skyrizi brought in sales upwards of $4.71 billion, which surpassed the previous estimates of $4.44 billion. Rinvoq sales also reached $2.18 billion, topping its estimates of $2.12 billion.1\n\n# What was AbbVie’s third quarter sales results? [...] # What was AbbVie’s third quarter sales results?\n\nAccording to AbbVie’s news release, the company earned quarterly profit-per-share of $1.86, which outperformed its estimates of $1.77-per-share. However, AbbVie said its quarterly results also include an negative impact of $1.50-per-share related to its acquired in-process research and development expenses.2\n\nAbbVie’s reported global net revenue from its immunology, neuroscience, oncology, and aesthetics portfolios were as follows: [...] Global Skyrizi: $4.708 billion, an increase of 46.8% on a reported basis, or 46.0% on an operational basis.\n Global Rinvoq: $2.184 billion, an increase of 35.3% on a reported basis, or 34.1% on an operational basis.\n Global Humira: $993 million, a decrease of 55.4% on a reported basis, or 55.7% on an operational basis.\n Global Vraylar: $934 million, an increase of 6.7%.\n Global Botox Therapeutic: $985 million, an increase of 16.1% on a reported basis, or 15.8% on an operational basis.\n\n# AbbVie’s investment into US-based manufacturing', 'score': 0.9999596, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://www.zacks.com/stock/news/2846507/heres-what-will-drive-abbvies-top-line-growth-in-2026', 'title': "Here's What Will Drive AbbVie's Top-line Growth in 2026", 'content': 'On the fourth-quarter conference call, management issued encouraging guidance for full-year 2026, expecting the top line to reach $67 billion, suggesting growth of about 9.5% over 2025 levels. This growth is largely expected to be driven by its newer immunology drugs, Rinvoq and Skyrizi. AbbVie anticipates one of its newer neuroscience drugs to achieve blockbuster status in sales this year.\n\nLet’s break it down.\n\n## ABBV to Generate Over $31B From Skyrizi & Rinvoq Sales [...] For the full-year 2026, AbbVie expects to record $12.5 billion from the neuroscience franchise, suggesting 16% growth over the 2025 levels. While Botox Therapeutic sales are expected to grow in the high single digit percent, the company projects double-digit growth in sales of other drugs. ABBV expects Vyalev to cross the $1 billion mark in global sales, which is encouraging for a drug that was launched last year in the United States. [...] It is mainly based on the robust commercial performance of Skyrizi and Rinvoq that AbbVie is projecting overall sales to increase at a high single-digit revenue CAGR through 2029. The company forecasts the combined sales of both these drugs to grow more than 20% year over year in 2026 — Skyrizi sales at about $21.5 billion and Rinvoq sales of around $10.1 billion.\n\nDespite generic erosion, AbbVie expects to record about $2.9 billion from Humira sales this year.\n\n## ABBV’s Neuroscience Franchise to Aid Sales Growth', 'score': 0.999892, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://intellectia.ai/news/monitor/abbvie-reports-strong-revenue-growth-amid-market-volatility', 'title': 'AbbVie reports strong revenue growth amid market volatility', 'content': "Loading...\n\nIntellectia Logo\nIntellectia\n\nSearch\n\n# AbbVie reports strong revenue growth amid market volatility\n\nABBV.N logo\n\nAbbVie Inc's stock fell 3.02% and hit a 20-day low amid a broader market decline, with the Nasdaq-100 down 0.12% and the S&P 500 down 0.24%.\n\nThe company's revenue from its new drugs Skyrizi and Rinvoq surged to $5 billion and $2.37 billion in Q4 2025, reflecting year-over-year increases of 32% and 29.5%, respectively. This strong performance supports AbbVie's transition following the loss of Humira's exclusivity, enhancing its long-term profitability and stability as a Dividend King.\n\nDespite the stock's decline, AbbVie's strong revenue growth indicates resilience in its business model, attracting investors seeking stability during market volatility.", 'score': 0.99983656, 'raw_content': None}, {'url': 'https://news.abbvie.com/2025-01-31-AbbVie-Reports-Full-Year-and-Fourth-Quarter-2024-Financial-Results', 'title': 'AbbVie Reports Full-Year and Fourth-Quarter 2024 Financial Results', 'content': "AbbVie is also updating its outlook for aesthetics revenues. The company now expects a high single-digit compound annual revenue growth rate for aesthetics through 2029. This guidance assumes 2025 as the base year in the compound annual growth rate calculation.\n\nAbout AbbVie\n\nAbbVie's mission is to discover and deliver innovative medicines that solve serious health issues today and address the medical challenges of tomorrow. We strive to have a remarkable impact on people's lives across several key therapeutic areas: immunology, oncology, neuroscience and eye care - and products and services across our Allergan Aesthetics portfolio. For more information about AbbVie, please visit us at www.abbvie.com. Follow @abbvie on X (formerly Twitter), Facebook, Instagram, YouTube or LinkedIn. [...] | a Represents net earnings attributable to AbbVie Inc. | [...] Long-Term Outlook\n\nAbbVie is reaffirming its expectations for a high single-digit compound annual revenue growth rate through 2029. This guidance assumes 2024 as the base year in the compound annual growth rate calculation.\n\nAbbVie is raising its long-term outlook for Skyrizi and Rinvoq revenues. The company now expects combined Skyrizi and Rinvoq 2027 revenues of more than $31 billion, an increase of approximately $4 billion compared to previous guidance for combined revenues of more than $27 billion in 2027. This guidance assumes Skyrizi revenues of more than $20 billion and Rinvoq revenues of more than $11 billion in 2027.", 'score': 0.9998247, 'raw_content': None}], 'response_time': 1.61, 'request_id': 'fb614e4d-f4de-468c-9747-9daf1e7034fa'}
